People wear protective face masks as they carry groceries in the centre of Brussels, amid the outbreak of COVID-19, caused by the novel coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - As the novel coronavirus continues to grow, more people may need to be put under home quarantine in order to stop the spread of the virus. The quarantine process typically entails two weeks that you are supposed to stay indoors without contact or exposure to anyone outside. In case of an emergency, health officials are recommending that people should ensure that they have an adequate supply of food, household supplies and diapers for small children. READ: Coronavirus in SA: Mkhize confirms Free State case not positive Before heading to stores to get more supplies than you need, you should start by taking inventory of things that you already have on hand. Consumers are also advised to focus on dry and canned foods which are easy to prepare. Below is a list of examples of the types of food one should stock up on, depending on dietary requirements: 1. Freezer meals, such as frozen vegetables including peas and sweetcorn, along with frozen fruits like pineapples and berries 2. Canned foods that contain liquid, such as tomatoes, beans, and tuna. 3. Wholewheat grains, such as bread, oats, and rice. 4. Nuts such as pecans, almonds, and walnuts. 5. Dry beans What is important to remember is that you need to create a sensible and nutritious list that will suit the needs of your household. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.